# AssessMate context (always apply)

Before planning or coding, load:

1. **`docs/NORTH_STAR.md`** — product source of truth  
2. **`docs/ROADMAP_AND_CHECKLIST.md`** — phases / SDLC / checklists  
3. **`docs/DOCUMENTATION_INDEX.md`** — discipline map + **Documentation Gate** (mandatory)

Also use when relevant: `docs/architecture/OVERVIEW.md`, `docs/architecture/DECISIONS.md`, `docs/design/UX_AND_ACCESSIBILITY.md` (**mandatory for any UI** — WCAG AA / 50s+ patterns; do not copy weak legacy affordances), `docs/quality/TESTING_AND_ANALYTICS.md`, `docs/learning/RUNBOOK.md`.

## UI / a11y non-negotiables (see UX doc for detail)

- Always-visible link/button affordances (not hover-only underlines).  
- Busy/loading until navigation finishes; errors alone are not enough.  
- Wizard step change: scroll to top + focus the step heading.  
- Dependent curriculum options: filter/disable/explain — never silent invalid combos.  

## Documentation Gate (do not skip)

After any non-trivial change, update the appropriate docs (ADR, UX/a11y, test log, learning runbook, ROADMAP ticks). A feature is not done until the Documentation Gate in ROADMAP/INDEX is satisfied.

## Non-negotiables

- Product: assessment papers + memos + cognitive/taxonomy reports for SA FET educators (Maths + Life Sciences).
- Primary users: Tanielle’s parents (50s+) — large text, plain language, wizard UX, teacher stays in control of AI output.
- **Mathematics ≠ Bloom’s.** Use CAPS cognitive levels: Knowledge 20%, Routine 35%, Complex 30%, Problem solving 15%. Dad’s GDE memo template is the Maths export gold standard.
- **Life Sciences** uses Bloom’s (+ IEB SAGS). Mom’s pain is diagrams + formatting (Arial 12, 1.5 spacing, PDF, lined paper).
- Stack: Next.js 16 App Router + TypeScript + Tailwind + **Supabase** (cloud Postgres). Do not require local PostgreSQL for MVP. Session file is `src/proxy.ts` (not deprecated middleware).
- Repo: `inmypurposetech-prog/assessment-builder`. Local: `~/Projects/assessmate`.
- Philosophy: question bank + workflow first; AI second. Budget-conscious (cheap models, RAG, free tiers).
- Template fidelity: educators upload packs (paper/memo/answer book/cognitive rules); visibility Private → School → later Public. Monetise template *slots/library* inside tiers — never archive-revival or storage-guilt fees.
- Dad Maths exemplar: `docs/parent-samples/mathematics/dbe/grade-12/` (June 2026 P2 + cognitive guide). Mom LS exemplar: `docs/parent-samples/life-sciences/ieb/grade-12/final-exam/2023/`.
- Solo founder wears all workplace disciplines (PO → Support) — see DOCUMENTATION_INDEX.
- **Git:** Branch first (`cursor/…` or `feature/…`), draft PR into `main`, then merge. Do **not** commit feature work straight to `main` (empty PRs). See ROADMAP SDLC → Branching and RUNBOOK R3.
- Out of MVP: SATAP Paper 2 packs, full PAT, SA-SAMS, B2G tenders, payments until parents validate.

